                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d273">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">852.2221/875: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bullitt</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-06-04T15:00:00-04:00"
                            >June 4, 1938—3 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>340. Reference Department’s 330 of June 1, 3 p.m. White informs us that his
                    organization is today announcing a general drive for funds <pb facs="0299"
                        n="291" xml:id="pg_291"/> to take care of American wounded in France.
                    Organization press release states “we proudly accept our responsibility to these
                    men”. With respect to 28 immediate cases White states appropriate instructions
                    have been sent to organization’s representative in Paris. We assume steps have
                    been taken to apply for necessary travel documents for these men. Consul
                    Marseille has reported names and data on eight wounded men in his district.</p>
                <p>Murphy<note n="57" xml:id="d273fn57">Robert Murphy, Consul and First Secretary of
                        Embassy in France.</note> sailed yesterday and has full information on this
                    whole matter.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Welles</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
